Motorists faced long tailbacks following an overturned car on the M8 Hundreds of drivers stuck following motorway accident Motorists faced long tailbacks following an overturned car on the M8The vehicle flipped on the eastbound carriageway between the Riddrie and Stepps Road junctions shortly before 7.00am this morning.Three lanes were closed while police and fire crews helped to recover the vehicle.Cars tailed back for miles, with traffic stretching as far as the Fruitmarket junction in Glasgow's city centre.The incident was cleared before 8.00am and it is understood there were no injuries. 